k numbers (aarch64, lima)\n\n| Mode | getpid | stat | open+close | lseek+read | write |\n|------|--------|------|------------|------------|-------|\n| rewrite | 0.5us | 25.5us | 93.6us | 23.1us | 30.2us |\n| trap | 9.1us | 26.2us | 162.8us | 78.6us | 51.4us |\n\nTrade-off: rewrite stat is 21x faster than seccomp on aarch64 (1.0us vs 21.1us with LKL inode cache), but open+close is 2.9x slower (113.6us vs 39.2us) due to in-process shadow FD creation.\n\n### Remaining work (tracked in TODO.md)\n\n- Per-syscall hybrid BPF filter: route metadata ops to RET_TRAP and file I/O to USER_NOTIF within a single filter (addresses the open+close regression).\n- Multi-threaded guests (CLONE_THREAD) blocked in trap/rewrite mode with ENOSYS; use `--syscall-mode=seccomp` for threaded workloads.\n- Full scan-on-X for JIT pages is deferred; W^X enforcement on mmap/mprotect rejects `PROT_WRITE|PROT_EXEC` in trap/rewrite mode, JIT pages fall through to Tier 1 RET_TRAP.\n- Caller-aware site classification before new inline fast paths (blanket virtual PID/TID inlining was reverted after breaking `raise(SIGUSR1)` via glibc's `tgkill`).\n\n---\n\nWant me to submit this comment, or do you want changes first?",
